    "state_reason": "completed",
    "title": "Possible UB in DeleteLock() function",
    "body": "Since #15233 has been merged, the `lockdata` becomes a static local variable with a well-defined initialization order: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/36c0abd8f61ba859d53b1e59014720282c97c143/src/sync.cpp#L93-L96\r\n\r\nIts destructor `~LockData()` [is called at program exit](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/program/exit).\r\n\r\nAt the same time, \"if a function-local ... static object was destroyed and then that function is called from the destructor..., the _behavior is undefined_.\"\r\n\r\nIt seems possible that at program exit the `lockdata` object is destroyed before a global `RecursiveMutex` destructor calls `DeleteLock()`, which in turn calls `GetLockData()` with UB.",
